org.jclouds.abiquo.domain.cloud

Class HardDisk

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jclouds.abiquo.domain.DomainWrapper<com.abiquo.server.core.infrastructure.storage.DiskManagementDto>
      • org.jclouds.abiquo.domain.cloud.HardDisk

  • public class HardDisk
extends DomainWrapper<com.abiquo.server.core.infrastructure.storage.DiskManagementDto>
    Represents a disk attached to a virtual machine.

    This disks will be created when a virtual machine is deployed, and will be destroyed when it is undeployed. If there is a need to use persistent storage, a persistent Volume should be used instead.

    Author:
    Ignasi Barrera
    See Also:
    http://community.abiquo.com/display/ABI20/Hard+Disks+Resource
